[
    {
        "text": "You might be surprised to find the idea...",
        "startTime": 427,
        "endTime": 2167,
        "slowStartTime": 790,
        "slowEndTime": 3475
    },
    {
        "text": "...behind the shorter length kilt as we know it today...",
        "startTime": 2248,
        "endTime": 4631,
        "slowStartTime": 3522,
        "slowEndTime": 7171
    },
    {
        "text": "...did not originate in Scotland.",
        "startTime": 4720,
        "endTime": 6261,
        "slowStartTime": 7230,
        "slowEndTime": 9617
    },
    {
        "text": "The idea actually came from an English Quaker called Thomas Rawlinson from Lancashire...",
        "startTime": 7628,
        "endTime": 12036,
        "slowStartTime": 11592,
        "slowEndTime": 18279
    },
    {
        "text": "...back in the 1720s.",
        "startTime": 12190,
        "endTime": 13688,
        "slowStartTime": 18435,
        "slowEndTime": 20757
    },
    {
        "text": "Rawlinson thought the great kilt was too much...",
        "startTime": 14995,
        "endTime": 17443,
        "slowStartTime": 22643,
        "slowEndTime": 26390
    },
    {
        "text": "...and he decided to split the garment...",
        "startTime": 17643,
        "endTime": 19121,
        "slowStartTime": 26615,
        "slowEndTime": 28906
    },
    {
        "text": "...and create one distinct piece running from the waist to the middle knee.",
        "startTime": 19229,
        "endTime": 22488,
        "slowStartTime": 28993,
        "slowEndTime": 33957
    },
    {
        "text": "Lo and behold, the small kilt,...",
        "startTime": 23779,
        "endTime": 25579,
        "slowStartTime": 35819,
        "slowEndTime": 38593
    },
    {
        "text": "...or in Gaelic, \"feileadh beag,\" pronounced \"feela beg\", was born.",
        "startTime": 25677,
        "endTime": 29200,
        "slowStartTime": 38665,
        "slowEndTime": 44025
    },
    {
        "text": "Rawlinson started wearing the small kilt and so did some of his peers.",
        "startTime": 30415,
        "endTime": 34235,
        "slowStartTime": 45772,
        "slowEndTime": 51577
    },
    {
        "text": "Before long, it was adopted by the Highlanders and even some Lowlanders.",
        "startTime": 35565,
        "endTime": 39413,
        "slowStartTime": 53498,
        "slowEndTime": 59345
    },
    {
        "text": "The Scottish kilt is bold, unique and unmatched by other garments.",
        "startTime": 40361,
        "endTime": 44495,
        "slowStartTime": 60692,
        "slowEndTime": 66967
    },
    {
        "text": "The garment usually wraps around the lower body, usually from the left hip,...",
        "startTime": 45742,
        "endTime": 49513,
        "slowStartTime": 68763,
        "slowEndTime": 74494
    },
    {
        "text": "...going around the front, and back around the front again to the opposite side,...",
        "startTime": 49679,
        "endTime": 53175,
        "slowStartTime": 74668,
        "slowEndTime": 79987
    },
    {
        "text": "...where it is then fastened.",
        "startTime": 53334,
        "endTime": 54639,
        "slowStartTime": 80151,
        "slowEndTime": 82184
    },
    {
        "text": "The kilt goes down from the hip to the middle of the knee.",
        "startTime": 55863,
        "endTime": 58662,
        "slowStartTime": 83945,
        "slowEndTime": 88218
    },
    {
        "text": "Moving swiftly on, the modern-day kilt is made of twill woven, worsted wool.",
        "startTime": 60102,
        "endTime": 64061,
        "slowStartTime": 90303,
        "slowEndTime": 96316
    },
    {
        "text": "The way it's woven creates a distinctive pattern known as tartan.",
        "startTime": 65453,
        "endTime": 68537,
        "slowStartTime": 98329,
        "slowEndTime": 103030
    },
    {
        "text": "Historically, specific patterns were associated with different clans and families.",
        "startTime": 69854,
        "endTime": 74472,
        "slowStartTime": 104931,
        "slowEndTime": 111933
    },
    {
        "text": "It wasn't until the Victorian era...",
        "startTime": 75773,
        "endTime": 77485,
        "slowStartTime": 113810,
        "slowEndTime": 116452
    },
    {
        "text": "...that specific patterns were systemically recorded and formalized.",
        "startTime": 77568,
        "endTime": 81138,
        "slowStartTime": 116502,
        "slowEndTime": 121932
    }
]